records.addlTxt:
Defendant Billy Ray Jackson in court with attorney Chris Bailey.  James W Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
The Court imposed the following:

AS TO COUNT 01:
The Court imposed but stayed 9 months at the House of Correction, credit for 5 days time served, Huber and good time allowed, and placed defendant on probation for one (1) year.  

AS TO COUNT 02:
The Court imposed but stayed 3 months at the House of Correction, consecutive to Count 1, with Huber for work; good time allowed, and placed defendant on probation for (1) year, concurrent to Count 1.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with co-defendant Keshawn Palmer;
 - No contact with the address of the offense at 2923 North 12th Street, city and county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin; no contact with any vacant or foreclosed on house;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Perform 50 hours community service;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Pay the DNA surcharges in Count 1 and 2, plus all costs and disbursements by the end of the probationary period.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

No restitution information was submitted; therefore, Court set restitution at zero.

